<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1876-06-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1876-06-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="157" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d157">
                        <head>No. 147.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1876-06-19"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 19,
                                1876</date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft"><hi rend="smallcaps">Fish</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington:</hi></p>
                        <p>Notified by Lord Derby that on Winslow’s discharge attorney-general
                            stated present condition of negotiations. To-day Brent discharged,
                            attorney-general confining himself, am informed by detectives, to same
                            statement.</p>
                        <closer><signed>HOFFMAN.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>